# SASS Installation Steps

1. (Optional) On Ubuntu, install Node.js v20.16 using:
   curl -o- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nvm-sh/nvm/v0.39.7/install.sh | bash
2. Exit the terminal using the `exit` command, then reopen it.
3. Make sure Node.js is installed (run `node -v`).
4. Install SASS using npm:
   npm install sass -v 3.7.4
5. Verify SASS installation (optional):
   npx sass --version
# SASS Installation Steps

1. Open your terminal in the project root directory.
2. (Optional) If using Ubuntu, install Node.js v20.16 with:
   curl -o- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nvm-sh/nvm/v0.39.7/install.sh | bash
   # Then exit and reopen the terminal.
3. Make sure Node.js is installed (node -v).
4. Install SASS using npm:
   npm install sass -v 3.7.4
5. Verify SASS installation:
   npx sass --version
